
[1]investigate

   INVEST'IGATE, v.t. [L. investigo; in and vestigo, to follow a track, to
   search; vestigium, a track or footstep.]

   To search into; to inquire and examine into with care and accuracy; to
   find out by careful disquisition; as, to investigate the powers and
   forces of nature; to investigate the causes of natural phenomena; to
   investigate the principles of moral duty; to investigate the conduct of
   an agent or the motives of a prince.
